The paper proposes a method for semi-supervised training of structured-output neural networks, which is a topic that falls under the broad category of machine learning (cs.LG). The experiments are conducted on image segmentation, which is a computer vision task (cs.CV). The proposed method involves training a discriminator network, which is a technique commonly used in generative models and falls under the category of adversarial learning (cs.AI). The paper also involves training neural networks, which is a topic in neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper involves natural language processing tasks such as named entity recognition and part-of-speech tagging, which fall under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL).
